What you need to know:

Transporters, herders, county officials and brokers (cartels) are among people one has to deal with in a long chain of actors before the meat reaches consumersThe pastoral communities sell bulls and non-performing females. One can buy them directly from the farmers, in the grazing fields or at watering points.Tertiary markets, on the other hand, are at slaughter premises far away from the production areas in places such as Mombasa and Nairobi.Tertiary markets in Nairobi include Dagoretti and Dandora (Njiru), which receive animals coming from secondary markets in North Eastern, Nyanza, Rift Valley and Eastern provinces.